Communication process. Beliefs and self-esteem. Verbal and non-verbal means of communication. Communication barriers. Communication skills: establishing contact, verbal self-expression, assertiveness, listening skills, relieving the stress situation and conflict mediation. Main competences of teamwork. Public speaking, speech as part of the communication culture. The role of voice, speech, facial expressions and body language when making presentations. Consistent breathing and effective presentations.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course gives an overview of the communication process and its management, how to analyse one's behaviour in communication and presentations, and develops the skills needed for communication and presentations individually and when working in groups.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student:  1) demonstrates the main communication competences in a practical communication process; 2) applies the rules and methods of compiling a speech; 3) analyses different communication situations and formulates feedforward; 4) reflects his presentation techniques, controls and models these consciously.
